   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2019 grant-Kakonge sch-classroom&amp;ablution</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ChildFund is an international NGO working in Zambia to help deprived, excluded and vulnerable children improve their lives and become responsible adults.  The purpose of the support was to help the community of Keyana in Shangombo District improve the infrastructure at Kakonge Primary School.  Keyana is a remote rural area with little access to basic social services.  Before the support, the school was made of mud and poles.  The project provided permanent infrastructure, water and sanitation facilities, teaching and learning materials and mechanisation of the borehole.  The school will service 400 children, 10 teachers and a community of about 3,000 people.</narrative>
  </description>
